{"name":"Schedule social posts with Google Sheets and WordPress with instant alerts","nodes":[{"parameters":{"rule":{"interval":[{"field":"weeks","triggerAtDay":[2],"triggerAtHour":9}]}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.scheduleTrigger","typeVersion":1.2,"position":[-270,400],"id":"691bf99f-2b99-462a-951c-7f67c168d481","name":"Weekly Schedule"},{"parameters":{"operation":"read","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Post Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[54,400],"id":"83441aba-0599-4530-85cc-aaa9f91f141c","name":"Read Content Calendar (Google Sheets)","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"conditions":{"options":{"caseSensitive":true,"leftValue":"","typeValidation":"strict","version":2},"conditions":[{"id":"579ebb33-ac72-4d03-80aa-67184f8d364f","leftValue":"={{ new Date($json.scheduledAt || 0) <= new Date() }}","rightValue":true,"operator":{"type":"boolean","operation":"true"}},{"id":"fd7029ac-c94a-48a9-90fb-d8816931153f","leftValue":"={{ $json.status }}","rightValue":"published","operator":{"type":"string","operation":"notEquals"}}],"combinator":"and"}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.filter","typeVersion":2.2,"position":[378,400],"id":"523d3851-500f-453b-9abf-6ded562a722e","name":"Due for Publishing?"},{"parameters":{"batchSize":1,"options":{"reset":false}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.splitInBatches","typeVersion":3,"position":[702,400],"id":"99352f89-53bb-43ab-8ba0-3ea1aa0cdcf3","name":"Post One at a Time"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#social","cachedResultName":"#social"},"text":"={{ $json.content }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[1026,880],"id":"efb395fa-0279-4096-a95d-f9ad64e20ff2","name":"Publish to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"amount":30,"unit":"seconds"},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.wait","typeVersion":1.1,"position":[1674,880],"id":"cbe05a15-a8ed-41f5-a2e9-8486323219d1","name":"Space Out Posts"},{"parameters":{"operation":"appendOrUpdate","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Post Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":["postId"],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[2646,880],"id":"cac37f1d-c2c1-4a3e-9851-8d22deda65a9","name":"Mark Row Published","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"aggregate":"aggregateAllItemData","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.aggregate","typeVersion":1,"position":[2970,400],"id":"89adf4c1-32db-4976-80e0-4ab94e46b474","name":"Count Published"},{"parameters":{"operation":"getCurrentDate","outputFieldName":"completedAt","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.dateTime","typeVersion":2,"position":[3294,400],"id":"9c10688b-024e-43e5-b650-6d19ccc29c05","name":"Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"dataToSave":{"values":[{"key":"runId","value":"={{ $execution.id }}"},{"key":"itemCount","value":"={{ $items().length }}"}]}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.executionData","typeVersion":1,"position":[3618,400],"id":"f7eeb396-0ddd-45cb-a725-2ab5da2664c9","name":"Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"method":"GET","url":"https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup","sendQuery":true,"queryParameters":{"parameters":[{"name":"query","value":"={{ $json.content }}"}]},"options":{"timeout":15000}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest","typeVersion":4.2,"position":[3942,400],"id":"a5b951e6-e6a1-43f8-8ec8-18768a599e45","name":"Enrich with Reference Data","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"alwaysOutputData":true,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"0ffa81ff-bdd8-4490-9bbf-b69ed46fee94","name":"enrichedAt","value":"={{ $now.toISO() }}","type":"string"},{"id":"932f24c5-3e94-4874-81f5-81de5ffdc9e8","name":"enrichmentSource","value":"reference-api","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[4266,400],"id":"b67df199-11a4-4373-84c7-83d8899c6aef","name":"Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"operation":"read","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Post Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[4590,400],"id":"8b692afc-0b9c-41b5-8b19-7b2a678c201c","name":"Load Previous Snapshot","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"alwaysOutputData":true,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"mode":"runOnceForAllItems","jsCode":"// Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\nconst current = $input.first().json;\nconst prev = $('Load Previous Snapshot').first().json || {};\nconst drift = {};\nfor (const k of Object.keys(current)) {\n  if (typeof current[k] === 'number' && typeof prev[k] === 'number' && prev[k] !== 0) {\n    drift[k] = Math.round(((current[k] - prev[k]) / prev[k]) * 1000) / 10;\n  }\n}\nreturn [{ json: { ...current, driftPct: drift, hasDrift: Object.values(drift).some(v => Math.abs(v) > 10) } }];"},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.code","typeVersion":2,"position":[4914,400],"id":"9cad0449-30c6-4fe2-a726-4d0b25415a37","name":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"mode":"runOnceForAllItems","jsCode":"// Build a stable idempotency key per post (djb2 hash, no deps)\nfunction hash(s) {\n  let h = 5381;\n  for (let i = 0; i < s.length; i++) h = ((h << 5) + h + s.charCodeAt(i)) >>> 0;\n  return h.toString(16);\n}\nreturn $input.all().map(item => {\n  const j = item.json;\n  return { json: { ...j, idempotencyKey: hash([j.postId, j.content].join('|')) } };\n});"},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.code","typeVersion":2,"position":[5238,400],"id":"22e5b597-816e-4ff7-bd07-b534ffd1098e","name":"Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"operation":"removeItemsSeenInPreviousExecutions","logic":"removeItemsWithAlreadySeenKeyValues","dedupeValue":"={{ $json.idempotencyKey }}","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.removeDuplicates","typeVersion":2,"position":[5562,400],"id":"66485730-29a8-4b1e-9170-f1af6051ad34","name":"Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"07f18fba-5638-4d40-9618-7c8be256cdb3","name":"runAt","value":"={{ $now.toISO() }}","type":"string"},{"id":"7571bd57-49c1-43a7-b788-6509bf3a6078","name":"itemCount","value":"={{ $input.all().length }}","type":"number"},{"id":"62b115de-3650-48d2-9e79-8faa12a6261b","name":"status","value":"completed","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5886,400],"id":"cf74c43c-be0b-42ce-b419-3f54c7811cbc","name":"Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Post Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[6210,400],"id":"76d601b4-d6ff-425d-aae4-103bf09c91ec","name":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#social","cachedResultName":"#social"},"text":"=✅ Schedule social posts with Google Sheets and WordPress with instant al — run completed at {{ $now.toFormat('HH:mm') }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[6534,400],"id":"72589fe3-b68a-41aa-b3cd-057e79ed5a34","name":"Send Summary to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"c0bd517a-1ec1-462a-8f00-550700d61ac0","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"e60b588c-ff4d-4a87-9654-afe5baad39fb","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"1412bae2-a4db-40c5-a8fd-df99ae4b71cf","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5886,1420],"id":"6fb78370-c2be-4217-a76e-e8c3050292a9","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#social","cachedResultName":"#social"},"text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[6210,1420],"id":"97f92000-f93a-4ce6-9c63-47fa4acb438d","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Post Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[6534,1420],"id":"326aebeb-6700-4298-b0ed-1c6abf2b764d","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Weekly Schedule\n\nStarts the workflow on a timer — weekly. No input data; downstream nodes fetch what they need.\n\nNext: Read Content Calendar (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"4ca77aea-6693-0c86-8305-012736080936","name":"Note: Weekly Schedule"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Read Content Calendar (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `read` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Due for Publishing? · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"405060a6-077e-ef2f-1735-2646d6933b83","name":"Note: Read Content Calendar (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Due for Publishing?\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Post One at a Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"d614f3c6-6b82-61c1-7a35-c43d97fc4aed","name":"Note: Due for Publishing?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Post One at a Time\n\nLoop controller — releases 1 item(s) per pass. Output 2 (loop) processes the batch, output 1 (done) fires after the last batch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Count Published · ②→ Publish to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"7c7e444b-fd40-2e41-a758-21ee0146c535","name":"Note: Post One at a Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Publish to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Space Out Posts · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,1000],"id":"fd656547-2984-809d-465f-394092257e37","name":"Note: Publish to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Space Out Posts\n\nPauses 30 seconds — spacing calls to respect rate limits.\n\nNext: Mark Row Published","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,1000],"id":"26b3fea9-c029-2db1-b0b5-aa609b4c92fd","name":"Note: Space Out Posts"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Mark Row Published\n\ngoogleSheets — `appendOrUpdate` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Post One at a Time · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,1000],"id":"7660ea20-4300-ba49-b598-9098222fc4c6","name":"Note: Mark Row Published"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Count Published\n\nCollapses all items into a single summary item (for counts and run stats).\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,520],"id":"a0dbff46-a561-2a32-7870-cfa618ab26c2","name":"Note: Count Published"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3234,520],"id":"03345541-ff17-0bd5-1ae9-ec4430924468","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,520],"id":"7689dc7b-60dd-9607-1e73-4d389009663c","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"0c84b12e-f3dd-f3e4-102b-8cae0c7d9145","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"05f971eb-024d-b67c-ccd4-1ac91ba8d5fd","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `read` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"24d5863d-2017-3980-dd97-98358c6a6ef3","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"ee708bb2-cf5f-b3d8-cfd5-d8a441cc00b1","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per post (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"83cc7818-5c66-9f42-e710-cdf81db1dde3","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"602f98b4-44ed-8579-1007-83c6150a997a","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"926ad4bb-7ce6-1ff3-c22b-bc45b4da5e3e","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"7dda03a0-6c1e-f76f-f104-6275ed557f37","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"55927bf5-2710-365e-cfd2-237e08e63bfd","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,1540],"id":"11ccbe96-e5f0-0979-d003-763ab96644cf","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,1540],"id":"af2e4742-fb7f-e5a2-0cc2-3b0f92279f77","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,1540],"id":"baf70561-9fd0-d495-3ca8-7b16531c32a2","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Schedule social posts with Google Sheets and WordPress with instant alerts\n\n**Pattern:** Social Scheduler · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nSchedule social posts with Google Sheets and WordPress with instant alerts. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual listening is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWeekly Schedule → Read Content Calendar (Google Sheets) → Due for Publishing? → Post One at a Time → Count Published → Stamp Completion Time → Persist Run Metadata → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to social scheduler without manual effort\n- Anyone automating listening in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Responds in seconds\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"f84a4717-811e-bab5-718b-ed610171b03a","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-20],"id":"002561d8-c7d0-882e-cfa8-bd3b4917d160","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-20],"id":"49836564-14d5-6d5f-b696-b1b33ce878bc","name":"⏱ Rate limiting"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-20],"id":"7fdc3845-a400-dcf4-3e4d-40c4b42f1226","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your listening process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-20],"id":"c62bf1c4-5710-b7fc-4794-735880e385c1","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Weekly Schedule":{"main":[[{"node":"Read Content Calendar (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Read Content Calendar (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Due for Publishing?","type":"main","i